attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Brian Chin, born in Kingston, Jamaica, enjoyed an early life in Port Royal, relishing sun-soaked beaches, simple joys by the harbor, and the legacy of Fort Charles. Relocating to Canada at six for better education, his family's culinary ties led to their ownership of Hibiscus Foods, known for delightful Jamaican patties. Despite studying marine biology, Brian took over the business in 2013, rebranding as Morgan's Harbour in 2019. He preserves his uncle's legacy, infusing it with innovation and a deep passion for crafting exquisite Jamaican patties.
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Morgan's Harbour offers an authentic Jamaican Patty experience in BC, inspired by Port Royal near Jamaica's capital. Committed to crafting exceptional Patties, we reject shortcuts for true flavour. Our artisanal approach revives the past's rich patty flavours lost to mass production. Using traditional methods and quality ingredients, we deliver a classic indulgence. With new ownership in 2013 came innovation, refining ingredients, removing preservatives, and introducing a remarkable Vegan patty. Every bite of a Morgan's Harbour patty blends the best of then and now, inviting you to savour a genuine Jamaican moment.

From our rich and savoury Jerk Chicken to the delightful spice of our Curry Chicken, and the hearty goodness of our Oxtail, our Jamaican Meals capture the essence of the island's culinary traditions. And don't miss out on our irresistible Jamaican Patties, available in a variety of flavours that dance with authentic Caribbean spices. Whether you're craving a hearty meal or a quick snack, our Jamaican cuisine is a journey for your taste buds that you won't want to miss. Come savour the Caribbean with Morgans Harbour today!

In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Brian Chin, born in Kingston, Jamaica, enjoyed an early life in Port Royal, relishing sun-soaked beaches, simple joys by the harbor, and the legacy of Fort Charles.
